  "@id": "ocp:github/phaserjs--phaser",
  "meta": {
    "title": "Phaser - HTML5 Game Framework",
    "description": "Phaser is a fun, free and fast 2D game framework for making HTML5 games for desktop and mobile web browsers, supporting Canvas and WebGL rendering.",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-11T04:21:22.656Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-11T04:21:22.656Z",
    "keywords": [
      "canvas",
      "discord-activities",
      "facebook-instant-games",
      "game-development",
      "game-frameworks",
      "gamedev",
      "html5-game-development",
      "javascript",
      "phaser",
      "phaser-development",
      "phaserjs",
      "webgl",
      "youtube-playables"
    ],
    "license": "MIT"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "![Phaser Banner](changelog/assets/phaser-banner.png \"Phaser Banner\")",
    "context": "![Phaser Banner](changelog/assets/phaser-banner.png \"Phaser Banner\")\n\n[![Discord](https://img.shields.io/discord/244245946873937922?style=for-the-badge)](https://discord.gg/phaser)\n![JSDelivr](https://img.shields.io/jsdelivr/npm/hm/phaser?style=for-the-badge)\n![GitHub](https://img.shields.io/github/downloads/phaserjs/phaser/total?style=for-the-badge)\n\nPhaser is a fast, free, and fun open source HTML5 game framework that offers WebGL and Canvas rendering across desktop and mobile web browsers and has been actively developed for over 10 years.\n\nGames can be built for the web, or as YouTube Playables, Discord Activities, Twitch Overlays or compiled to iOS, Android, Steam and native apps using 3rd party tools. You can use JavaScript or TypeScript for development. Phaser supports over 40 different front-end frameworks including React and Vue.\n\nPhaser is commercially developed and maintained by **Phaser Studio Inc** along with our fantastic open source community. As a result of rapid support, and a developer friendly API, Phaser is currently one of the [most starred](https://github.com/collections/javascript-game-engines) game frameworks on GitHub.\n\nInterested in learning more? Click the image below to watch our intro video.\n\n[![YouTube](http://i.ytimg.com/vi/jHTRu4iNTcA/maxresdefault.jpg)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jHTRu4iNTcA)",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
